To access the osname.data in step2.dart, you can use the FutureBuilder widget just like in welcome.dart.

Here is how you can modify the step2 function in step2.dart to include the FutureBuilder:

Step step2(BuildContext context, int currentStep, Function incrementStep) {
  return Step(
    title: Text('Step 2: Theme intensity'),
    content: FutureBuilder<String>(
      future: Executable.getOSName(),
      builder: (BuildContext context, AsyncSnapshot<String> osname) {
        if (osname.connectionState == ConnectionState.waiting) {
          return CircularProgressIndicator();
        } else {
          // Check if osname.data is not equal to "Floflis"
          if (osname.data != "Floflis") {
            // If it's not "Floflis", return an empty Container (equivalent to display:none)
            return Container();
          } else {
            // If it's "Floflis", return the original Column widget
            return Column(
              children: <Widget>[
                // ... existing widgets ...
              ],
            );
          }
        }
      },
    ),
  );
}

This code will check if osname.data is not equal to "Floflis". If it's not, it will return an empty Container (which is equivalent to display:none in CSS). If it is "Floflis", it will return the original Column widget with all the existing widgets inside it.

